Here's how to save and restore draft text using Window lifecycle events:

**Create a custom `Window` subclass in `App.xaml.cs`:**

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
        => new AppWindow(new AppShell());
}

public class AppWindow : Window
{
    public AppWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }

    protected override void OnStopped()
    {
        base.OnStopped();
        SaveDraft();
    }

    protected override void OnDestroying()
    {
        base.OnDestroying();
        SaveDraft(); // Android back-button can skip Stopped
    }

    protected override void OnResumed()
    {
        base.OnResumed();
        if (Shell.Current?.CurrentPage is NotePage notePage)
            notePage.ViewModel.DraftText = Preferences.Get("draft_text", string.Empty);
    }

    private void SaveDraft()
    {
        if (Shell.Current?.CurrentPage is NotePage notePage)
            Preferences.Set("draft_text", notePage.ViewModel.DraftText);
    }
}
```

**In your `NotePage` ViewModel, restore on first load too:**

```csharp
public class NoteViewModel : INotifyPropertyChanged
{
    private string _draftText = string.Empty;

    public string DraftText
    {
        get => _draftText;
        set { _draftText = value; OnPropertyChanged(); }
    }

    public NoteViewModel()
    {
        // Restore any previously saved draft
        DraftText = Preferences.Get("draft_text", string.Empty);
    }
    // ... INotifyPropertyChanged implementation
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`OnStopped`** fires when the app is fully backgrounded — save here.
- **`OnDestroying`** also saves because Android's back button can skip `Stopped`.
- **`OnResumed`** fires when returning from background (not on first launch).
- **Keep handlers fast** (< 2 seconds) — `Preferences` is ideal for small text. For large drafts, use `File.WriteAllTextAsync` to a known path instead.
- **`Resumed` doesn't fire on first launch** — that's why the ViewModel constructor also reads from `Preferences`.
